      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لَهُ رَجُلٌ تَزَوَّجَ اِمْرَأَةً بِحُكْمِهَا فَمَاتَ قَبْلَ أَنْ تَحْكُمَ قَالَ \"لَيْسَ لَهَا صَدَاقٌ وَ هِيَ تَرِثُهُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5673 - Ibn Abi Nasr narrated from Abdul Karim ibn Amr, from Muhammad ibn Muslim, from Abu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), who said:\nI asked Imam (as) about a man who married a woman according to her own condition (by her terms), but he died before she could set the conditions.\nImam (as) said: \"She is not entitled to a dowry (ṣadaq), but she inherits from him.\""
        ]
      }
    },
